0one%20rights%20group%20said%20was%20unprecedented.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20execution%2C%20on%20Saturday%20in%20the%20southwestern%20region%20of%20Najran%2C%20was%20of%20a%20Yemeni%20national%20convicted%20of%20smuggling%20drugs%20into%20the%20Gulf%20kingdom%2C%20the%20official%20Saudi%20Press%20Agency%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20brought%20to%20101%20the%20number%20of%20foreigners%20executed%20so%20far%20in%202024%2C%20according%20to%20the%20tally%20which%20is%20compiled%20from%20state%20media%20reports.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20almost%20triple%20the%20figures%20for%202023%20and%202022%2C%20when%20Saudi%20authorities%20had%20put%20to%20death%2034%20foreigners%20each%20year%2C%20according%20to%20AFP%20tallies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Berlin-based%20European-Saudi%20Organisation%20for%20Human%20Rights%20(ESOHR)%20said%20this%20year's%20executions%20had%20already%20broken%20a%20record.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20the%20largest%20number%20of%20executions%20of%20foreigners%20in%20one%20year.%20Saudi%20Arabia%20has%20never%20executed%20100%20foreigners%20in%20a%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Taha%20al-Hajji%2C%20the%20group's%20legal%20director.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESaudi%20Arabia%20has%20faced%20persistent%20criticism%20over%20its%20use%20of%20the%20death%20penalty%2C%20which%20human%20rights%20groups%20have%20condemned%20as%20excessive%20and%20out%20of%20step%20with%20efforts%20to%20soften%20its%20forbidding%20image%20and%20welcome%20international%20tourists%20and%20investors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20oil-rich%20kingdom%20executed%20the%20third%20highest%20number%20of%20prisoners%20in%20the%20world%20after%20China%20and%20Iran%20in%202023%2C%20according%20to%20Amnesty%20International.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20September%2C%20AFP%20reported%20that%20Saudi%20Arabia%20had%20carried%20out%20its%20highest%20number%20of%20executions%20in%20more%20than%20three%20decades%2C%20surpassing%20its%20previous%20highs%20of%20196%20in%202022%20